comment._content: The J.M.S. 'Aki Maru' was at No.7 Wharf, Walsh Bay from 8-25 December 1919. Arrival - trove.nla.gov.au/ndp/del/article/15868280 Passengers inbound - trove.nla.gov.au/ndp/del/article/15864704 Departure (6am, 25/12/1919) and passenger list - trove.nla.gov.au/ndp/del/article/15881274 Trove makes it too easy, assuming it is 1919. The 'Aki Maru' was a regular visitor at the time.

comment.author: 32162360@N00
comment._content:
Wait up!

I thought 16 days rather long to turn around in Sydney.  The 'Aki Maru'  went on to Melbourne on 11/12/1919 and returned to Sydney on 16/12/1919.
